Program: Free Thinking
Title: Arundhati Roy
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b08slx9t
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 6 Mar 2018
Arundhati Roy, the Man Booker prize winning author and campaigner, is in conversation with Philip Dodd about a life in the public eye and the novel she published 20 years after The God of Small Things. Arundhati Roy's second novel is called The Ministry of Utmost Happiness. Producer: Zahid Warley. Show less